    <section>
        <h2>About the Film</h2>
        <p><em>Memoria y Pérdida</em> follows the journey of migrants crossing the U.S.-Mexico border, exploring the trauma, resilience, and humanitarian efforts of groups like Border Angels.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Visual Style</h2>
        <p>Using poetic imagery, observational cinematography, and archival footage, the film immerses viewers in the emotional and physical landscape of migration.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
        <h2>Director’s Statement</h2>
        <p>This film is a deeply personal exploration of migration, inspired by my mother’s journey and the stories of those who continue to cross these dangerous landscapes.</p>
